7.2 The augmented Lagrangian formulation of FSI

In this section, we summarize the FSI formulation proposed in [74], which generates the methods detailed in Sections 7.3 and 7.4.3 as special cases. For simplicity, we proceed with a treatment that is most directly applicable to incompressible Navier–Stokes ﬂow for the ﬂuid subproblem and compressible hyperelasticity for the solid subproblem, but the ideas related to the coupling of these problems generalize in a straightforward way to other models.

